	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />So it's double region coded. Not only does your TV have to be PAL for Years Behind to even work, but it also has to be a CRT to display the hidden message. CRTs sold in NTSC-land are usually NTSC-only, unlike LCDs where it's just as cheap to recognize, parse, and upscale both NTSC and PAL as it is to make separate firmwares per region.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


